OL,3,CMan with chronic neurological
OL,4,Ccondition brands benefits overhaul
OL,5,C'offensive'
OL,7,FDavid Colley, 60, has told ITV News
OL,8,FTyne Tees that he suffers around 30
OL,9,Fseizures a month and receives Personal
OL,10,FIndependence Payments (PIP).
OL,12,FHe believes that the reforms unveiled
OL,13,Fby the Work and Pensions Secretary in
OL,14,Fthe Commons on Tuesday lunchtime (18
OL,15,FMarch) portray disabled people as
OL,16,F"scroungers".
OL,18,FLiz Kendall has outlined radical
OL,19,Fchanges which aim to get more people
OL,20,Finto work and save #5 billion by 2030.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/9
