OL,7,F"But we're not prepared to stand back
OL,8,Fand do nothing while millions of
OL,9,Fpeople ` especially young people ` who
OL,10,Fhave potential to work and live
OL,11,Findependent lives, instead become
OL,12,Ftrapped out of work and abandoned by
OL,13,Fthe system.
OL,15,F"It would be morally bankrupt to let
OL,16,Ftheir life chances waste away."
OL,18,FMs Kendall, who was flanked in the
OL,19,FCommons by Sir Keir and Deputy Prime
OL,20,FMinister Angela Rayner, told MPs: "We
OL,21,Fwere elected on a mandate for change.
